1
00:00:54,793 --> 00:00:55,528
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:55,528 --> 00:00:56,328
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:56,328 --> 00:00:57,062
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:57,062 --> 00:00:57,796
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:03,602
I know what you're thinking.

6
00:01:03,602 --> 00:01:05,037
In your imagination,

7
00:01:06,071 --> 00:01:08,207
I've already died at your hands...

8
00:01:09,041 --> 00:01:10,142
countless times.

9
00:01:10,609 --> 00:01:11,443
Imagination?

10
00:01:13,312 --> 00:01:15,748
You dying at my hands is reality.

11
00:01:16,081 --> 00:01:17,116
It's only a matter of time.

12
00:01:18,717 --> 00:01:19,518
Is that so?

13
00:01:21,420 --> 00:01:23,022
You've run away.

14
00:01:24,290 --> 00:01:26,759
Hiding in there like that,
hoping you'll be forgotten...

15
00:01:27,459 --> 00:01:28,561
like an idiot,

16
00:01:29,695 --> 00:01:31,330
living on edge.

17
00:01:32,932 --> 00:01:33,666
Okay.

18
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:36,669
I guess that's how it might look.

19
00:01:39,538 --> 00:01:41,073
I'm not that smart,

20
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,409
so I hadn't thought that far ahead.

21
00:01:44,276 --> 00:01:45,544
Cut the bullshit.

22
00:01:46,579 --> 00:01:48,814
As long as I'm alive,
that'll never happen.

23
00:01:48,814 --> 00:01:50,115
But here's the thing.

24
00:01:51,584 --> 00:01:52,952
In this world,

25
00:01:54,386 --> 00:01:56,856
nothing is ever as certain
as you make it sound.

26
00:01:57,189 --> 00:01:58,257
Even you...

27
00:01:59,024 --> 00:02:00,226
could change.

28
00:02:01,327 --> 00:02:02,495
So don't be so quick to...

29
00:02:06,298 --> 00:02:08,767
You mean a girl like me
couldn't possibly do anything?

30
00:02:09,001 --> 00:02:11,136
You're just messing around with me...

31
00:02:11,136 --> 00:02:13,506
thinking I'll just ramble on
until I wear myself out and drop.

32
00:02:14,673 --> 00:02:15,574
Right?

33
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:21,881
Are you insane?

34
00:02:23,048 --> 00:02:24,316
Is it finally sinking in?

35
00:02:26,085 --> 00:02:27,153
Over just this?

36
00:02:29,121 --> 00:02:30,122
I promise you.

37
00:02:31,991 --> 00:02:33,926
You will die at my hands...

38
00:02:35,794 --> 00:02:37,796
no matter what. I swear it.

39
00:02:42,368 --> 00:02:45,571
(Chase)

40
00:02:49,575 --> 00:02:52,578
(CEO Ryu Jun Ho)

41
00:03:02,388 --> 00:03:04,623
Here's the guest list
for next month's groundbreaking ceremony.

42
00:03:05,491 --> 00:03:07,993
We're planning to send invitations
to carefully selected allies.

43
00:03:09,094 --> 00:03:11,096
What should we do about the vice chairman?

44
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:16,936
He called in the head of legal yesterday
and seems to have given some order.

45
00:03:17,503 --> 00:03:19,638
He keeps digging around into your affairs.

46
00:03:20,239 --> 00:03:22,842
I heard he even ordered
a major expansion of the legal team...

47
00:03:22,842 --> 00:03:24,043
He's a diligent man, that's why.

48
00:03:25,878 --> 00:03:27,847
What should we do about the invitations?

49
00:03:29,181 --> 00:03:30,349
Proceed as planned.

50
00:03:30,349 --> 00:03:32,685
He's still the vice chairman
at headquarters, after all.

51
00:03:33,519 --> 00:03:34,353
Yes, sir.

52
00:03:35,287 --> 00:03:36,121
And...

53
00:03:37,056 --> 00:03:39,391
could you find out
where the vice chairman is right now?

54
00:04:15,127 --> 00:04:17,663
We'll meet when the time comes anyway.

55
00:04:18,998 --> 00:04:20,399
So what kind of rude stunt is this?

56
00:04:20,966 --> 00:04:21,834
My apologies.

57
00:04:22,835 --> 00:04:25,070
As for the person
you were supposed to meet today,

58
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:27,072
I asked for their understanding.

59
00:04:27,072 --> 00:04:29,742
It seems you and I...

60
00:04:30,509 --> 00:04:32,912
are having a communication problem,
Vice Chairman.

61
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:34,980
Between me and you,

62
00:04:35,648 --> 00:04:37,750
what communication is needed?

63
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,352
When Mono Architecture was founded,

64
00:04:41,587 --> 00:04:44,657
it was agreed that if the target revenue
was reached within three years,

65
00:04:44,657 --> 00:04:46,158
the shares owned by the company...

66
00:04:46,158 --> 00:04:48,427
would be transferred to Mono Architecture.

67
00:04:48,994 --> 00:04:51,630
And the terms of the transfer
would be decided by mutual agreement.

68
00:04:52,064 --> 00:04:54,433
That's stated quite clearly
in the company's articles of association.

69
00:04:56,836 --> 00:04:57,937
As of last March,

70
00:04:58,904 --> 00:05:01,006
we met the target revenue.

71
00:05:01,006 --> 00:05:03,409
Please honor the agreement.

72
00:05:03,409 --> 00:05:05,611
With the chairman dead,

73
00:05:06,946 --> 00:05:08,180
this is what you bring up?

74
00:05:08,414 --> 00:05:09,215
Vice Chairman.

75
00:05:09,215 --> 00:05:10,950
It may not seem like much to you,

76
00:05:12,718 --> 00:05:14,820
but our company
is in a state of emergency.

77
00:05:16,455 --> 00:05:19,992
The founder was found
reduced to ashes overnight...

78
00:05:20,459 --> 00:05:21,927
burned completely black...

79
00:05:22,761 --> 00:05:25,030
beyond recognition.

80
00:05:25,698 --> 00:05:26,565
And yet,

81
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:28,801
the police are still...

82
00:05:30,236 --> 00:05:32,738
investigating the cause of his death.

83
00:05:34,306 --> 00:05:35,307
So I have no choice...

84
00:05:36,542 --> 00:05:38,377
but to prepare for the possibility...

85
00:05:38,978 --> 00:05:40,379
that it wasn't a simple accident.

86
00:05:41,113 --> 00:05:42,915
Because we live in a world
where common sense doesn't apply...

87
00:05:45,217 --> 00:05:46,152
like right now.

88
00:05:46,452 --> 00:05:47,319
Vice Chairman.

89
00:05:47,319 --> 00:05:49,722
You don't need
to take my words so personally,

90
00:05:50,523 --> 00:05:52,424
because it's not just me.

91
00:05:54,059 --> 00:05:55,761
It's the company's official position.

92
00:05:56,395 --> 00:05:59,498
I understand you've been poking around...

93
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:04,603
and looking into my background.

94
00:06:05,838 --> 00:06:07,506
Let's stop wasting...

95
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,009
each other's time.

96
00:06:12,378 --> 00:06:13,746
Are you giving me orders?

97
00:06:20,219 --> 00:06:21,654
You may be...

98
00:06:23,389 --> 00:06:25,157
my senior in this industry, Vice Chairman,

99
00:06:27,226 --> 00:06:29,595
but I'm out of patience now.

100
00:06:33,365 --> 00:06:34,300
From here on out,

101
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:37,369
even I don't know what I might do.

102
00:06:38,037 --> 00:06:39,171
So you too,

103
00:06:39,705 --> 00:06:40,773
on your own,

104
00:06:41,373 --> 00:06:43,142
should think before you act.

105
00:06:43,576 --> 00:06:44,443
You little punk!

106
00:06:48,047 --> 00:06:49,014
Well then,

107
00:06:49,014 --> 00:06:51,750
I'll consider this
a productive conversation,

108
00:06:52,518 --> 00:06:53,786
and take my leave.

109
00:07:40,466 --> 00:07:42,334
Have you ever really felt anxious?

110
00:07:52,878 --> 00:07:55,447
The kind where everything collapses
in an instant,

111
00:07:58,617 --> 00:08:00,119
and you're terrified...

112
00:08:00,119 --> 00:08:02,254
someone might do that to your life.

113
00:08:07,526 --> 00:08:08,561
Sometimes,

114
00:08:10,262 --> 00:08:12,631
I want to let go of everything.

115
00:08:16,435 --> 00:08:17,937
I'm just too exhausted.

116
00:08:22,875 --> 00:08:24,109
It's too hard.

117
00:08:31,817 --> 00:08:33,486
I shouldn't have gone.

118
00:08:35,454 --> 00:08:36,322
That day,

119
00:08:40,392 --> 00:08:42,461
I went somewhere I never should have.

120
00:08:43,395 --> 00:08:44,196
Do you see that?

121
00:08:45,331 --> 00:08:46,198
Yeah.

122
00:08:46,198 --> 00:08:47,466
That's where we went.

123
00:08:48,033 --> 00:08:48,901
I see.

124
00:08:54,974 --> 00:08:55,875
He's here.

125
00:08:56,675 --> 00:08:57,877
Myo Jin, let's go.

126
00:09:03,182 --> 00:09:05,384
Ryu Jun Ho.

127
00:09:09,788 --> 00:09:12,124
I missed you.

128
00:09:24,703 --> 00:09:25,838
What do you think?

129
00:09:28,374 --> 00:09:29,208
Tell me.

130
00:09:34,513 --> 00:09:35,781
What's with these furnitures?

131
00:09:37,216 --> 00:09:40,653
They're not what I asked you to order.

132
00:09:40,653 --> 00:09:41,654
Why?

133
00:09:41,854 --> 00:09:43,422
They're almost exactly what you described,

134
00:09:44,123 --> 00:09:45,191
just more expensive.

135
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:47,693
What happened...

136
00:09:49,962 --> 00:09:52,498
to everything I said?

137
00:09:52,832 --> 00:09:55,100
I told you, I picked better pieces.

138
00:09:55,701 --> 00:09:56,468
You don't like it?

139
00:09:56,468 --> 00:09:58,404
It's not that I don't like it. It's wrong.

140
00:10:00,239 --> 00:10:02,541
I told the contractor
every detail myself...

141
00:10:02,541 --> 00:10:03,876
and even wrote it all down,

142
00:10:03,876 --> 00:10:05,444
and you overturned every bit of it.

143
00:10:05,444 --> 00:10:07,046
Are you getting mad at me right now?

144
00:10:11,851 --> 00:10:13,219
If you hate it that much,

145
00:10:18,123 --> 00:10:19,191
throw them all out.

146
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:23,963
Tear it all apart
and fill it with what you want.

147
00:10:25,297 --> 00:10:26,198
Problem solved.

148
00:10:26,632 --> 00:10:28,801
Architecture isn't just the exterior.

149
00:10:28,801 --> 00:10:30,536
The interior is part
of the architecture too.

150
00:10:30,936 --> 00:10:32,738
This may be a vacation house
for you and me,

151
00:10:32,738 --> 00:10:33,739
but...

152
00:10:33,739 --> 00:10:35,908
it's still one of my works in Korea.

153
00:10:36,308 --> 00:10:37,343
That's right.

154
00:10:37,810 --> 00:10:40,446
This is a space just for the two of us.

155
00:10:41,881 --> 00:10:43,582
I love it just the way it is.

156
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:47,086
If I'm happy with it,
shouldn't you be too?

157
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,662
Please, can you stop
playing the perfectionist...

158
00:10:57,863 --> 00:10:59,365
for once?

159
00:11:00,399 --> 00:11:01,233
Please.

160
00:11:03,903 --> 00:11:05,104
You greedy young man.

161
00:11:10,943 --> 00:11:11,811
Say hi.

162
00:11:12,144 --> 00:11:13,412
That's my friend, Myo Jin.

163
00:11:25,591 --> 00:11:26,692
You know who he is, right?

164
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,403
You have a house like this
in every country?

165
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:39,572
The others were all built to be sold,

166
00:11:40,673 --> 00:11:41,941
but not this one.

167
00:11:45,711 --> 00:11:48,781
I heard who designed this place,
so I said I wanted it.

168
00:11:49,215 --> 00:11:50,049
The design?

169
00:11:52,017 --> 00:11:53,352
Half of it was done by someone else.

170
00:11:54,587 --> 00:11:55,588
Are we really doing this again?

171
00:11:57,022 --> 00:11:57,823
Cheers.

172
00:12:03,429 --> 00:12:06,499
But your father is really impressive.

173
00:12:07,066 --> 00:12:09,235
I can't even imagine...

174
00:12:09,235 --> 00:12:10,369
how huge his business must be.

175
00:12:12,071 --> 00:12:14,740
Myo Jin is so curious about my dad.

176
00:12:15,674 --> 00:12:17,376
She talks about him to me all the time.

177
00:12:21,847 --> 00:12:22,815
But...

178
00:12:23,282 --> 00:12:24,216
the two of you...

179
00:12:26,385 --> 00:12:27,586
are so alike.

180
00:12:28,554 --> 00:12:29,488
In what way?

181
00:12:29,488 --> 00:12:30,789
The way you two admire my dad.

182
00:12:31,857 --> 00:12:33,459
You say it all the time too,

183
00:12:33,459 --> 00:12:35,094
that you want to be
as successful as my dad.

184
00:12:37,429 --> 00:12:39,365
Myo Jin says it every chance she gets too,

185
00:12:39,365 --> 00:12:40,900
that she wants to meet my dad.

186
00:12:43,269 --> 00:12:44,103
Really?

187
00:12:44,436 --> 00:12:46,205
Was I like that?

188
00:12:46,205 --> 00:12:47,072
Yeah.

189
00:12:47,072 --> 00:12:49,742
He said he'd be coming
to Korea before long anyway,

190
00:12:50,242 --> 00:12:51,410
so I guess you'll get your chance then.

191
00:12:51,911 --> 00:12:53,112
The three of us should meet him together.

192
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:55,381
Is he planning to come?

193
00:12:55,948 --> 00:12:58,551
I don't know. Maybe he just says that.

194
00:13:00,719 --> 00:13:01,587
Cheers.

195
00:13:27,313 --> 00:13:28,814
I'm just going to run to the bath...

196
00:13:50,169 --> 00:13:51,103
Ms. Ham.

197
00:13:52,171 --> 00:13:53,339
I'm sorry.

198
00:13:53,339 --> 00:13:55,608
I thought you were Hee Su.

199
00:13:56,075 --> 00:13:57,543
It's okay.

200
00:13:57,543 --> 00:13:58,711
It was my fault.

201
00:13:59,044 --> 00:14:00,646
I shouldn't have borrowed
Hee Su's clothes.

202
00:14:01,814 --> 00:14:03,516
I didn't know I'd be staying until today.

203
00:14:04,517 --> 00:14:05,518
I'm sorry.

204
00:14:06,752 --> 00:14:07,920
I'm not even drunk,

205
00:14:08,521 --> 00:14:10,156
and I still made that mistake.

206
00:14:10,856 --> 00:14:11,857
I'm sorry.

207
00:14:14,827 --> 00:14:16,195
Jun Ho.

208
00:14:17,329 --> 00:14:19,565
Did we finish all the champagne?

209
00:14:20,699 --> 00:14:21,867
There's none left?

210
00:14:28,474 --> 00:14:31,977
That looks great on you.

211
00:14:32,711 --> 00:14:34,346
You should've changed sooner.

212
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:35,981
Right.

213
00:14:36,282 --> 00:14:38,017
Why are you all by yourself?
Isn't that boring?

214
00:14:38,517 --> 00:14:39,418
Let's drink more.

215
00:14:40,419 --> 00:14:41,520
I'm done.

216
00:14:41,987 --> 00:14:43,255
I'm going to get some air.

217
00:14:43,255 --> 00:14:44,123
Why?

218
00:14:44,557 --> 00:14:45,524
Are you feeling stuffy?

219
00:14:46,392 --> 00:14:48,427
Should we take the yacht out to sea then?

220
00:14:48,627 --> 00:14:50,930
No. You two spend some time together.

221
00:15:13,752 --> 00:15:14,553
Stop.

222
00:15:14,820 --> 00:15:15,688
Stop.

223
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:18,390
Why?

224
00:15:19,592 --> 00:15:20,626
I said stop.

225
00:15:23,429 --> 00:15:24,396
Why, all of a sudden?

226
00:15:28,634 --> 00:15:29,869
The air is off.

227
00:15:32,238 --> 00:15:33,339
Everything feels different.

228
00:15:50,523 --> 00:15:51,724
Are you still taking the pills?

229
00:15:53,259 --> 00:15:54,160
Why?

230
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:55,861
Are you worried?

231
00:15:58,831 --> 00:16:00,733
What are you doing? Give me that.

232
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:02,001
Let go of this. Are you crazy?

233
00:16:02,001 --> 00:16:04,336
I told you not to keep
increasing the dose on your own.

234
00:16:12,044 --> 00:16:12,878
You...

235
00:16:14,613 --> 00:16:16,148
really are crazy.

236
00:16:18,851 --> 00:16:20,319
You haven't forgotten...

237
00:16:21,821 --> 00:16:23,155
what Dad told you, have you?

238
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:25,791
He's not giving you the gifts...

239
00:16:27,693 --> 00:16:29,461
for nothing.

240
00:16:31,931 --> 00:16:32,832
You know that, right?

241
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:18,744
Get in.

242
00:17:19,178 --> 00:17:20,012
Excuse me?

243
00:17:20,546 --> 00:17:21,514
I said get in.

244
00:17:59,118 --> 00:18:00,986
Is something going on
between you and Hee Su?

245
00:18:02,154 --> 00:18:04,924
Since when have you been
so close with Hee Su?

246
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,428
You probably know...

247
00:18:10,930 --> 00:18:13,065
that she's not easy to get close to.

248
00:18:19,839 --> 00:18:20,773
She's...

249
00:18:21,941 --> 00:18:22,975
my friend.

250
00:18:23,776 --> 00:18:24,643
Hee Su...

251
00:18:25,544 --> 00:18:28,214
seems to really care about you, Ms. Ham.

252
00:18:29,048 --> 00:18:29,982
What is it...

253
00:18:31,650 --> 00:18:33,052
that you like about Hee Su?

254
00:18:35,821 --> 00:18:37,456
Please be understanding, Mr. Ryu.

255
00:18:39,024 --> 00:18:42,061
When women haven't seen their lover
in a while, they fuss a little.

256
00:18:43,562 --> 00:18:45,130
Hee Su is just...

257
00:18:46,265 --> 00:18:47,833
more soft-hearted than other women.

258
00:18:58,744 --> 00:18:59,745
You seem to know...

259
00:19:00,713 --> 00:19:01,847
quite a lot about Hee Su.

260
00:19:03,782 --> 00:19:05,184
You should go back now.

261
00:19:06,986 --> 00:19:09,188
I'll stay out a little longer.

262
00:19:09,588 --> 00:19:10,856
Aren't you curious?

263
00:19:13,425 --> 00:19:14,260
About what?

264
00:19:14,693 --> 00:19:16,662
Whether what happened earlier
was really an accident.

265
00:19:19,498 --> 00:19:21,100
I know you know...

266
00:19:23,802 --> 00:19:25,204
it wasn't, Ms. Ham.

267
00:19:26,839 --> 00:19:28,107
Go back.

268
00:19:29,141 --> 00:19:30,910
I don't want to cause
pointless misunderstandings.

269
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:33,245
What misunderstanding?

270
00:20:28,534 --> 00:20:31,437
I stole Jun Ho away from Hee Su.

271
00:20:33,105 --> 00:20:34,573
I was out of my mind.

272
00:20:35,808 --> 00:20:38,043
I betrayed my friendship with Hee Su,

273
00:20:38,777 --> 00:20:40,646
hid it as if nothing had happened,

274
00:20:40,646 --> 00:20:42,314
and pretended not to know anything.

275
00:20:49,955 --> 00:20:50,990
Did Hee Su...

276
00:20:51,957 --> 00:20:52,825
really...

277
00:20:56,028 --> 00:20:57,630
know nothing?

278
00:21:28,794 --> 00:21:30,329
Were you at the beach?

279
00:21:38,337 --> 00:21:39,305
Yeah.

280
00:21:50,649 --> 00:21:52,017
What took you so long?

281
00:21:54,286 --> 00:21:55,254
Well,

282
00:21:55,855 --> 00:21:58,190
I stayed out a bit longer than I meant to.

283
00:21:59,325 --> 00:22:00,526
It looks like you had fun.

284
00:22:06,532 --> 00:22:07,466
What about Jun Ho?

285
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:08,601
What?

286
00:22:08,834 --> 00:22:11,136
Did you see Jun Ho?

287
00:22:12,404 --> 00:22:14,406
I thought he was heading
toward the beach, too.

288
00:22:16,242 --> 00:22:18,043
I wouldn't know.

289
00:22:24,683 --> 00:22:25,718
Isn't it funny?

290
00:22:27,987 --> 00:22:30,156
What is?

291
00:22:30,789 --> 00:22:32,458
Everyone thinks...

292
00:22:35,027 --> 00:22:37,129
they're faster than the tide.

293
00:22:38,831 --> 00:22:39,932
But seawater...

294
00:22:41,867 --> 00:22:43,435
rushes in faster than you'd think.

295
00:22:45,271 --> 00:22:47,239
By the time you realize it,
it'll already be too late.

296
00:22:48,707 --> 00:22:49,775
Before you know it,

297
00:22:51,043 --> 00:22:52,845
you're already in over your head.

298
00:23:00,286 --> 00:23:01,420
So...

299
00:23:01,787 --> 00:23:02,855
be careful.

300
00:23:13,432 --> 00:23:14,567
You must be tired too.

301
00:23:37,756 --> 00:23:39,058
This is yours, right, Ms. Ham?

302
00:23:43,162 --> 00:23:44,029
Give it to me.

303
00:23:44,563 --> 00:23:45,698
Hee Su was right.

304
00:23:47,032 --> 00:23:47,833
About what?

305
00:23:48,267 --> 00:23:50,069
She said you're a very good painter,

306
00:23:50,669 --> 00:23:52,071
and that I should buy
your work in advance.

307
00:23:53,339 --> 00:23:54,573
Hee Su was joking.

308
00:23:56,909 --> 00:23:58,811
Don't you know
Hee Su never jokes like that?

309
00:24:01,647 --> 00:24:04,216
Ms. Ham, do you paint people too?

310
00:24:04,817 --> 00:24:07,186
If you need a portrait,
please ask Hee Su.

311
00:24:09,321 --> 00:24:10,723
She's much better at it than I am.

312
00:24:11,924 --> 00:24:13,492
Of course Hee Su is good too,

313
00:24:14,493 --> 00:24:15,327
but...

314
00:24:16,929 --> 00:24:18,497
I'm curious about your work.

315
00:24:23,836 --> 00:24:24,803
One mistake...

316
00:24:25,437 --> 00:24:26,672
was enough.

317
00:24:27,239 --> 00:24:30,176
I'm in so much pain I want to die,
so stop playing these games.

318
00:24:32,077 --> 00:24:34,580
- Ms. Ham.
- Even this talk makes me uncomfortable.

319
00:24:35,548 --> 00:24:37,216
You said you're going to Seoul
tomorrow morning, right?

320
00:24:39,084 --> 00:24:40,352
I'm going tomorrow too.

321
00:24:41,253 --> 00:24:42,421
My office...

322
00:24:43,455 --> 00:24:45,124
isn't far from Hee Su's house.

323
00:24:45,124 --> 00:24:47,126
- Please, stop...
- Mono Architecture.

324
00:24:48,194 --> 00:24:49,962
It'll come up in your GPS,
so come by anytime.

325
00:25:02,942 --> 00:25:04,043
Trash.

326
00:25:06,745 --> 00:25:09,682
I was trash and a devil to Hee Su.

327
00:25:12,751 --> 00:25:13,986
I ruined everything,

328
00:25:13,986 --> 00:25:15,788
and I stabbed Hee Su in the back.

329
00:25:23,629 --> 00:25:26,499
Do you know what it's like
to be born into a pit...

330
00:25:28,534 --> 00:25:29,435
of desert sand?

331
00:25:31,203 --> 00:25:32,738
You wash your body with sand,

332
00:25:34,940 --> 00:25:37,309
eat sand like it's food,

333
00:25:40,146 --> 00:25:42,581
and die with that grit
grinding through you.

334
00:25:46,152 --> 00:25:48,154
That's me now.

335
00:25:54,693 --> 00:25:56,695
Jun Ho betrayed Hee Su too.

336
00:25:58,697 --> 00:26:01,367
He deceived her and broke her,
just like I did.

337
00:26:04,069 --> 00:26:06,438
We made a choice we can never take back,

338
00:26:08,307 --> 00:26:10,576
and Hee Su suffered to death all alone.

339
00:26:14,446 --> 00:26:17,349
Ugly beasts named
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho...

340
00:26:18,217 --> 00:26:19,652
killed Hee Su.

341
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:26,692
She must have been so lonely
and in so much pain.

342
00:26:36,135 --> 00:26:37,136
Even now,

343
00:26:39,839 --> 00:26:41,607
I want to pay the price.

344
00:27:39,598 --> 00:27:40,733
Why did you do this?

345
00:27:45,638 --> 00:27:47,873
Setting aside whether it's good or bad,

346
00:27:47,873 --> 00:27:51,177
this is nothing more than
a piece made for personal gratification.

347
00:27:52,578 --> 00:27:54,313
There isn't a single element...

348
00:27:54,313 --> 00:27:56,148
that fits the traditional
object-based style.

349
00:28:01,187 --> 00:28:02,054
Thank you.

350
00:28:03,722 --> 00:28:07,760
You've understood my intent exactly, sir.

351
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:11,030
This project is about building
the largest museum in Asia...

352
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:12,898
here in Korea.

353
00:28:13,499 --> 00:28:16,936
Not only in scale, but in artistry,
technical skill, and creativity,

354
00:28:16,936 --> 00:28:17,903
in every way,

355
00:28:18,404 --> 00:28:21,173
it will become a benchmark
for Korean architecture.

356
00:28:21,173 --> 00:28:22,374
With a design like this,

357
00:28:23,909 --> 00:28:26,712
what exactly can you claim
as your strength, Mr. Ryu?

358
00:28:27,346 --> 00:28:28,180
Sir,

359
00:28:29,315 --> 00:28:32,918
when most architects begin a new project,

360
00:28:33,886 --> 00:28:36,789
they start by referencing past typologies.

361
00:28:37,423 --> 00:28:40,092
But as an architect,

362
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,495
I reject that approach.

363
00:28:42,495 --> 00:28:45,431
Too much confidence
can come off as arrogance.

364
00:28:45,431 --> 00:28:47,800
Repeated reference to past cases...

365
00:28:49,401 --> 00:28:51,871
only leads to
the accumulation of imitation.

366
00:28:52,938 --> 00:28:55,207
If we cannot break free from that frame,

367
00:28:55,207 --> 00:28:57,042
Korean architecture will eventually...

368
00:28:57,042 --> 00:28:59,245
harden into a series of similar forms.

369
00:29:00,813 --> 00:29:03,382
You may criticize my work,

370
00:29:05,184 --> 00:29:07,720
but the more efforts and attempts
like mine accumulate,

371
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:08,754
the more Korean architecture...

372
00:29:10,789 --> 00:29:12,925
will break free from self-replication.

373
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:17,363
That's why for this museum,

374
00:29:17,363 --> 00:29:19,698
I chose "Silence for Essence"
as the concept.

375
00:29:21,634 --> 00:29:24,103
By thoroughly eliminating
the interference...

376
00:29:24,103 --> 00:29:26,472
and imposed functions
of conventional buildings,

377
00:29:26,472 --> 00:29:29,375
I want to focus...

378
00:29:30,075 --> 00:29:31,844
on faithfully holding the people, music,

379
00:29:31,844 --> 00:29:34,780
and essence of life within it.

380
00:29:46,725 --> 00:29:49,094
(Made in China,
HGA Distribution Co., Ltd.)

381
00:29:51,063 --> 00:29:52,898
Speak clearly, you bastard.

382
00:29:53,933 --> 00:29:55,734
What did I do so wrong?

383
00:29:56,001 --> 00:29:57,436
All I did was...

384
00:29:57,870 --> 00:29:59,605
take a little nap after lunch.
Is that such a crime?

385
00:29:59,872 --> 00:30:03,209
I gave my work to other guys instead.

386
00:30:03,843 --> 00:30:07,513
So in the end, I didn't cause any loss.

387
00:30:07,513 --> 00:30:08,380
That's what I'm saying.

388
00:30:09,248 --> 00:30:12,384
That bastard sure talks a lot.

389
00:30:13,686 --> 00:30:15,855
If beating up
a perfectly fine site manager...

390
00:30:16,388 --> 00:30:18,557
isn't wrong, then what is?

391
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:23,629
That site manager had it in for me.

392
00:30:23,929 --> 00:30:26,532
He's always trailing behind me...

393
00:30:27,032 --> 00:30:28,701
and picking fights
whenever he gets a chance.

394
00:30:29,502 --> 00:30:30,769
What was I supposed to do?

395
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:33,038
There's a limit...

396
00:30:34,807 --> 00:30:36,108
to how much a person can take.

397
00:30:36,108 --> 00:30:37,576
Hey.

398
00:30:37,810 --> 00:30:38,711
Are you a credit card...

399
00:30:39,278 --> 00:30:40,112
to have a limit?

400
00:30:41,046 --> 00:30:43,082
It's nice to meet a bastard
even dumber than me.

401
00:30:43,415 --> 00:30:45,151
Listen to him ramble
like he's something special.

402
00:30:45,417 --> 00:30:47,920
Hey, if you're getting paid,
just do the work you're told.

403
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:49,155
While everyone else was working,

404
00:30:49,155 --> 00:30:51,123
what was so great about you
lying there asleep by yourself...

405
00:30:51,123 --> 00:30:52,992
to beat a man up over that, you bastard?

406
00:30:53,726 --> 00:30:54,760
Do you want me to show you how it's done?

407
00:30:55,394 --> 00:30:56,328
Do you?

408
00:30:56,529 --> 00:30:57,730
I'll split your whole unit.

409
00:31:00,466 --> 00:31:02,468
Did everything I told you
already vanish from that thick skull?

410
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,304
What was it you told me?

411
00:31:05,604 --> 00:31:07,840
That ignorant bastard is stupid too.

412
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,341
That's exactly why
he keeps causing trouble.

413
00:31:10,876 --> 00:31:13,913
If you go around acting like a thug
in someone else's country,

414
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:16,515
all our people get cursed for it.

415
00:31:16,515 --> 00:31:18,117
Didn't I say that?

416
00:31:22,021 --> 00:31:25,090
The reason Korean Chinese folks like us
don't get treated right...

417
00:31:25,090 --> 00:31:26,592
is because idiots like him...

418
00:31:26,592 --> 00:31:29,128
keep causing trouble for other people.

419
00:31:29,728 --> 00:31:30,896
Didn't I say that?

420
00:31:30,896 --> 00:31:32,198
You don't remember a thing?

421
00:31:32,565 --> 00:31:33,866
I remember.

422
00:31:35,935 --> 00:31:36,969
I remember.

423
00:31:36,969 --> 00:31:37,837
What?

424
00:31:39,538 --> 00:31:41,040
So you remembered and still did it?

425
00:31:45,044 --> 00:31:46,011
Then,

426
00:31:46,645 --> 00:31:47,680
because of you,

427
00:31:49,281 --> 00:31:51,851
our fellow Korean Chinese
are going to get cursed again.

428
00:31:53,886 --> 00:31:54,987
How are you going
to take responsibility for that?

429
00:31:55,254 --> 00:31:56,956
Boss, I'm sorry.

430
00:31:57,857 --> 00:32:00,759
From now on, I won't even eat or work out.

431
00:32:00,759 --> 00:32:01,961
I'll only work.

432
00:32:05,498 --> 00:32:06,932
That blockheaded bastard.

433
00:32:07,299 --> 00:32:09,802
Keep him reflecting on what he did
until I say otherwise.

434
00:32:09,802 --> 00:32:11,770
Boss, please spare me.

435
00:32:12,037 --> 00:32:13,239
I'm sorry.

436
00:32:13,239 --> 00:32:14,840
Please, just spare me this once.

437
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:15,741
Boss.

438
00:32:15,975 --> 00:32:16,842
Boss!

439
00:32:17,543 --> 00:32:19,278
- Please spare me.
- Shut your mouth.

440
00:32:19,545 --> 00:32:21,313
People will think
you're being dragged off to die.

441
00:32:22,148 --> 00:32:24,250
Boss.

442
00:32:25,317 --> 00:32:26,252
Boss.

443
00:32:27,052 --> 00:32:28,387
We've got a problem.

444
00:32:28,387 --> 00:32:29,388
Hae Sik...

445
00:32:30,122 --> 00:32:32,558
got beaten by some gangsters
and hauled off to the hospital.

446
00:32:32,558 --> 00:32:34,360
Who this time?

447
00:32:34,827 --> 00:32:36,662
Your younger brother, Hae Sik.

448
00:32:44,837 --> 00:32:45,938
This isn't fair.

449
00:32:47,339 --> 00:32:49,308
I even got disciplined at work today,

450
00:32:50,342 --> 00:32:52,711
and now look at the state I'm in.

451
00:32:53,312 --> 00:32:55,247
Is what you told me all there is to say?

452
00:32:55,781 --> 00:32:57,449
So you did absolutely nothing wrong?

453
00:32:57,449 --> 00:32:58,617
Don't you know me, Hae Kwang?

454
00:32:59,819 --> 00:33:02,955
Have you ever seen me
go around making trouble?

455
00:33:03,389 --> 00:33:04,256
Because of me,

456
00:33:05,257 --> 00:33:07,326
has our people ever lost face,

457
00:33:07,326 --> 00:33:08,294
even once?

458
00:33:08,828 --> 00:33:10,196
Have I ever, even once...

459
00:33:12,865 --> 00:33:14,466
Even seeing me like this,

460
00:33:15,267 --> 00:33:17,536
you're saying
you still can't trust your brother?

461
00:33:20,539 --> 00:33:22,141
Do you remember where it was?

462
00:33:22,141 --> 00:33:24,143
I don't know where the ones
who did this to me are,

463
00:33:24,710 --> 00:33:26,846
but I do know
where the guy who drugged our drinks is.

464
00:33:27,980 --> 00:33:29,648
My friend gets discharged tomorrow,

465
00:33:30,583 --> 00:33:32,151
so you can ask him.

466
00:33:33,018 --> 00:33:34,720
Why didn't you say anything until now?

467
00:33:35,087 --> 00:33:37,456
You obviously just got back from home
after a long time.

468
00:33:37,890 --> 00:33:39,792
This is nothing to be proud of.

469
00:33:42,027 --> 00:33:45,231
It's humiliating enough
getting beaten up in a foreign country.

470
00:33:46,365 --> 00:33:47,399
If people start saying...

471
00:33:47,933 --> 00:33:49,635
I'm an idiot,

472
00:33:50,269 --> 00:33:52,204
what happens to my pride?

473
00:33:52,204 --> 00:33:53,138
Your pride?

474
00:33:53,539 --> 00:33:56,475
Then out of all those guys,
why did you get beaten the worst?

475
00:33:58,077 --> 00:34:00,146
If I don't look out
for my own people, who will?

476
00:34:00,746 --> 00:34:01,647
Do you think...

477
00:34:01,647 --> 00:34:04,350
I wanted to get beaten like this?

478
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:09,054
It hurts.

479
00:34:10,156 --> 00:34:11,190
Fine.

480
00:34:14,693 --> 00:34:16,228
Look at the mess you're in.

481
00:34:20,833 --> 00:34:21,767
Hey.

482
00:34:21,767 --> 00:34:24,737
Who's that bitch hanging around with now?

483
00:34:24,737 --> 00:34:27,006
She'll be contacting you again
before long, won't she?

484
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:30,209
Just give me the signal when she does,

485
00:34:30,209 --> 00:34:31,710
and I'll take care
of everything after that.

486
00:34:34,513 --> 00:34:36,715
How many times
do I have to say this to you?

487
00:34:36,715 --> 00:34:38,551
I'm repeating the same thing
like a parrot.

488
00:34:39,418 --> 00:34:40,319
If...

489
00:34:40,719 --> 00:34:42,521
that woman comes here,

490
00:34:43,022 --> 00:34:44,623
and I tell you about it,

491
00:34:46,525 --> 00:34:48,527
you'll handle it yourself, is that it?

492
00:34:48,527 --> 00:34:49,829
And you'll just...

493
00:34:50,362 --> 00:34:52,331
sit back and enjoy the show.

494
00:34:52,898 --> 00:34:53,933
Why?

495
00:34:54,500 --> 00:34:55,334
What?

496
00:34:55,668 --> 00:34:57,770
Why drag me into something...

497
00:34:58,137 --> 00:34:59,538
you can do by yourself?

498
00:35:00,339 --> 00:35:01,674
What are you saying?

499
00:35:02,041 --> 00:35:03,175
Do you want me to spell it out?

500
00:35:13,919 --> 00:35:15,387
If that woman dies,

501
00:35:17,590 --> 00:35:20,059
you'll be the one who did it,

502
00:35:20,426 --> 00:35:22,628
but the blood will end up on my hands.

503
00:35:22,895 --> 00:35:24,864
If you act alone,

504
00:35:25,264 --> 00:35:26,098
since...

505
00:35:26,966 --> 00:35:29,268
I would know it was your doing,

506
00:35:31,637 --> 00:35:33,339
you'd be afraid of what comes after.

507
00:35:33,639 --> 00:35:37,143
And after getting rid of her,
you'd have to get rid of me too.

508
00:35:38,377 --> 00:35:40,012
So...

509
00:35:41,180 --> 00:35:42,515
you've been thinking it over.

510
00:35:44,083 --> 00:35:45,784
That's why, from the start,

511
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:50,055
you want to pull me in.

512
00:35:52,091 --> 00:35:54,293
No, I think you've got the wrong idea.

513
00:35:54,293 --> 00:35:56,495
You think you can play
a shallow game like that?

514
00:35:58,030 --> 00:36:00,065
Someone like you who became
the driver for a wealthy family...

515
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:04,003
from a day laborer on construction sites?

516
00:36:09,742 --> 00:36:11,177
Bring money!

517
00:36:12,444 --> 00:36:14,180
Whatever your angle is,

518
00:36:14,180 --> 00:36:16,148
I'll do exactly what you want.

519
00:36:18,784 --> 00:36:19,985
Did you already forget...

520
00:36:20,619 --> 00:36:22,488
what it takes to get me moving?

521
00:36:30,462 --> 00:36:33,866
If you come empty-handed one more time
and try that slick shit with me,

522
00:36:34,934 --> 00:36:36,268
not that woman,

523
00:36:37,269 --> 00:36:39,338
but you will die at my hands first.

524
00:36:42,641 --> 00:36:44,477
If you understand, then get out.

525
00:36:47,179 --> 00:36:48,280
I'm tired.

526
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:08,200
You're still awake?

527
00:37:15,174 --> 00:37:16,108
Are you okay?

528
00:37:17,042 --> 00:37:18,410
There's something I want to ask.

529
00:37:19,745 --> 00:37:21,247
Will you answer me honestly?

530
00:37:24,216 --> 00:37:25,050
Yeah.

531
00:37:26,018 --> 00:37:26,886
What is it?

532
00:37:34,593 --> 00:37:36,061
It's about Choi Hee Su.

533
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:40,833
Why haven't you told me until now
about the relationship between you two?

534
00:37:44,036 --> 00:37:46,305
- Myo Jin.
- "Just someone you barely know?"

535
00:37:47,806 --> 00:37:48,707
How...

536
00:37:49,642 --> 00:37:51,610
How could you lie like that?

537
00:37:54,914 --> 00:37:57,750
It was too hard for you to take
because you were in treatment, Myo Jin.

538
00:38:00,986 --> 00:38:03,489
You abandoned Hee Su,
who was your girlfriend,

539
00:38:04,256 --> 00:38:05,958
and I betrayed Hee Su, who was my friend.

540
00:38:05,958 --> 00:38:07,259
Is that what you call "too hard?"

541
00:38:08,694 --> 00:38:09,528
No.

542
00:38:10,696 --> 00:38:12,932
That's something I need to know.

543
00:38:15,234 --> 00:38:16,001
Myo Jin.

544
00:38:16,001 --> 00:38:17,803
You said you couldn't tell me
because you were afraid it would shock me,

545
00:38:18,437 --> 00:38:20,773
and that you'd tell me everything
once I got better.

546
00:38:21,907 --> 00:38:24,677
Was that all about Hee Su,
who was abandoned by trash like us,

547
00:38:25,678 --> 00:38:28,247
and then died in an accident?

548
00:38:43,195 --> 00:38:44,029
I'm sorry.

549
00:38:46,932 --> 00:38:48,167
I was selfish.

550
00:38:55,875 --> 00:38:58,010
But I wasn't trying to hide it on purpose.

551
00:38:58,944 --> 00:39:00,646
How could I?

552
00:39:03,516 --> 00:39:06,652
Those are memories
that would've come back eventually.

553
00:39:07,653 --> 00:39:09,889
It was hard for me to say,

554
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:12,158
and for you, Myo Jin,

555
00:39:13,025 --> 00:39:14,426
it would be hard to hear.

556
00:39:16,162 --> 00:39:17,096
I think...

557
00:39:18,264 --> 00:39:19,632
I just wanted to put it off
a little longer.

558
00:39:21,133 --> 00:39:22,401
This is all my fault.

559
00:39:24,703 --> 00:39:26,572
Hee Su was struggling.

560
00:39:28,874 --> 00:39:31,977
She said everyone around her
only wanted to use her,

561
00:39:31,977 --> 00:39:33,212
and that she was all alone.

562
00:39:34,547 --> 00:39:35,581
The only people...

563
00:39:36,448 --> 00:39:38,617
she thought she could trust
were you and me.

564
00:39:39,685 --> 00:39:41,954
Hee Su was already wavering.

565
00:39:48,894 --> 00:39:50,563
Every time I try to do anything,

566
00:39:50,563 --> 00:39:52,498
things keep going wrong.

567
00:40:05,211 --> 00:40:06,712
What happened to Hee Su?

568
00:40:08,214 --> 00:40:10,883
The investigation is still underway,
so we'll learn in time.

569
00:40:11,450 --> 00:40:14,687
What was I doing there that day?

570
00:40:16,489 --> 00:40:17,756
Like the detective said,

571
00:40:18,390 --> 00:40:20,759
no matter how hard I think about
why my accident happened near the villa,

572
00:40:21,961 --> 00:40:23,963
I just can't remember.

573
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:35,541
What?

574
00:40:35,774 --> 00:40:37,910
Choi Hee Su's account was deleted.

575
00:40:38,244 --> 00:40:40,379
Forensics had a rough time finding this.

576
00:40:40,813 --> 00:40:43,682
Come on, she's a young woman
with U.S. citizenship.

577
00:40:43,682 --> 00:40:45,618
How could she have no social media?

578
00:40:46,185 --> 00:40:47,520
Someone must've wiped it.

579
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:49,989
She could've deleted it herself.

580
00:40:50,923 --> 00:40:52,158
It was after the incident.

581
00:40:52,791 --> 00:40:53,859
That's when it was deleted.

582
00:40:54,293 --> 00:40:55,127
No way.

583
00:41:00,966 --> 00:41:02,835
Choi Hee Su and Ham Myo Jin
knew each other?

584
00:41:03,435 --> 00:41:04,303
Friends?

585
00:41:05,237 --> 00:41:07,339
Hey, what does this look like to you?

586
00:41:08,174 --> 00:41:10,075
This was taken to celebrate an engagement.

587
00:41:11,177 --> 00:41:12,178
Choi Hee Su...

588
00:41:13,045 --> 00:41:13,979
and Ryu Jun Ho?

589
00:41:15,548 --> 00:41:17,149
That Ham Myo Jin...

590
00:41:17,783 --> 00:41:18,918
is seriously creepy.

591
00:41:19,451 --> 00:41:22,221
She kept insisting
she didn't know anything,

592
00:41:22,221 --> 00:41:23,722
and here's the reason.

593
00:41:25,357 --> 00:41:27,626
After Choi Hee Su died in an accident,

594
00:41:27,626 --> 00:41:29,762
her friend Ham Myo Jin
stepped right into her place?

595
00:41:32,264 --> 00:41:34,466
But she keeps denying it
with that same old routine.

596
00:41:35,801 --> 00:41:37,770
Maybe there's really
something wrong with her head.

597
00:41:41,674 --> 00:41:43,843
You took time out
of your busy schedule for me,

598
00:41:44,210 --> 00:41:45,845
so I hope you like it.

599
00:41:46,445 --> 00:41:49,215
I've booked dinner
at a very special place.

600
00:41:51,217 --> 00:41:52,251
When have you ever...

601
00:41:52,885 --> 00:41:54,520
done anything that wasn't special?

602
00:42:02,228 --> 00:42:03,696
The way things are looking,

603
00:42:03,696 --> 00:42:07,733
Oh Sang Il will likely become
head of the judging panel.

604
00:42:09,001 --> 00:42:12,505
The other judges are unanimously
recommending him too.

605
00:42:13,005 --> 00:42:14,206
Not just me,

606
00:42:14,206 --> 00:42:17,009
but everyone in the industry is on edge.

607
00:42:17,009 --> 00:42:18,277
On edge? Please.

608
00:42:19,178 --> 00:42:20,613
There are only a few firms...

609
00:42:20,946 --> 00:42:23,482
that can handle
a project like this anyway.

610
00:42:25,518 --> 00:42:27,052
I will make sure this goes successful.

611
00:42:27,319 --> 00:42:30,689
I know your abilities well, Mr. Cho.

612
00:42:32,558 --> 00:42:33,492
But tell me,

613
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,229
do you happen to know Ryu Jun Ho?

614
00:42:37,897 --> 00:42:39,398
He's still young,

615
00:42:39,398 --> 00:42:40,799
but he has the fundamentals.

616
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:43,202
He hasn't been back in Korea long,

617
00:42:43,569 --> 00:42:45,604
but the projects he's done
aren't bad either.

618
00:42:46,972 --> 00:42:48,207
But why do you ask?

619
00:42:48,474 --> 00:42:50,643
I heard that young man...

620
00:42:50,643 --> 00:42:52,878
secretly met with CEO Oh Sang Il.

621
00:42:54,180 --> 00:42:55,714
The timing is rather sensitive, isn't it?

622
00:42:56,882 --> 00:42:58,751
He doesn't have
enough domestic work history,

623
00:42:58,751 --> 00:43:00,352
so he shouldn't even qualify to apply.

624
00:43:00,352 --> 00:43:01,921
The qualifications were already announced.

625
00:43:02,888 --> 00:43:03,956
You know that next week,

626
00:43:03,956 --> 00:43:06,992
the judging panel
is being announced, right?

627
00:43:07,226 --> 00:43:08,093
Yes, Assemblyman.

628
00:43:08,928 --> 00:43:09,795
At that time,

629
00:43:11,664 --> 00:43:15,134
I think the revised clause
will be announced as well.

630
00:43:15,601 --> 00:43:18,938
Oh Sang Il personally requested it
from the other judges.

631
00:43:19,672 --> 00:43:21,740
He said there should be
merit-based judging...

632
00:43:21,740 --> 00:43:23,943
without sacred cows or discrimination.

633
00:43:24,577 --> 00:43:25,444
That does sound...

634
00:43:26,078 --> 00:43:28,314
exactly like CEO Oh.

635
00:43:29,815 --> 00:43:31,116
Even if it's you,

636
00:43:31,817 --> 00:43:33,586
don't get too complacent.

637
00:43:34,620 --> 00:43:36,989
There's always a back door somewhere.

638
00:43:47,032 --> 00:43:48,067
I'm sorry...

639
00:43:49,635 --> 00:43:52,037
for barging in
during your break like this.

640
00:43:52,037 --> 00:43:53,672
Like your memories, Ms. Ham?

641
00:43:58,844 --> 00:44:01,113
Before Jun Ho met me,

642
00:44:01,113 --> 00:44:03,182
he was already engaged to someone.

643
00:44:05,017 --> 00:44:06,886
I was friends with her.

644
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:08,921
I don't know why I did it,

645
00:44:10,823 --> 00:44:13,626
but I ended up realizing
that I stole her fiancé.

646
00:44:18,864 --> 00:44:20,633
I wandered around...

647
00:44:20,633 --> 00:44:22,701
as if I'd find something profound,

648
00:44:25,137 --> 00:44:26,639
and the memory I found...

649
00:44:29,275 --> 00:44:30,376
was that I was trash.

650
00:44:34,513 --> 00:44:35,314
Doctor,

651
00:44:36,715 --> 00:44:39,218
is there any point
in continuing my treatment?

652
00:44:41,587 --> 00:44:42,555
Tell me...

653
00:44:43,055 --> 00:44:45,758
the honest thought
inside your heart, Ms. Ham.

654
00:44:47,593 --> 00:44:48,661
I'm afraid.

655
00:44:50,763 --> 00:44:52,965
I'm already in so much pain I want to die,

656
00:44:55,034 --> 00:44:56,769
and if there's still
something worse waiting,

657
00:44:57,703 --> 00:44:58,804
if that's really true...

658
00:44:58,804 --> 00:45:01,440
All of this is for you to decide, Ms. Ham.

659
00:45:02,107 --> 00:45:03,876
It always has been.

660
00:45:04,910 --> 00:45:06,412
I've only helped from the side...

661
00:45:06,412 --> 00:45:07,546
in a very limited way.

662
00:45:09,782 --> 00:45:12,117
Human memory becomes distorted.

663
00:45:12,751 --> 00:45:14,753
Initial memories...

664
00:45:14,753 --> 00:45:16,489
are almost never preserved intact...

665
00:45:16,489 --> 00:45:17,690
for anyone.

666
00:45:18,357 --> 00:45:19,558
Distortion?

667
00:45:20,593 --> 00:45:23,062
Time changes everything.

668
00:45:23,662 --> 00:45:25,231
Memory is no different.

669
00:45:26,966 --> 00:45:30,102
In a case like yours,
after such a major accident,

670
00:45:30,736 --> 00:45:33,672
we need to judge
the situation more carefully.

671
00:45:35,241 --> 00:45:37,243
Stealing your friend's lover,

672
00:45:37,243 --> 00:45:39,311
and then saying
you don't know why you did it...

673
00:45:39,945 --> 00:45:41,780
is avoidance or an excuse.

674
00:45:42,882 --> 00:45:44,283
Doctor, that really isn't...

675
00:45:44,283 --> 00:45:45,951
I know. It's neither.

676
00:45:46,252 --> 00:45:48,354
As a doctor, the Myo Jin I know...

677
00:45:50,990 --> 00:45:52,324
truly doesn't know...

678
00:45:52,324 --> 00:45:54,293
why she acted that way.

679
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:55,961
Then...

680
00:45:55,961 --> 00:45:57,129
It will be hard,

681
00:45:57,129 --> 00:45:59,298
but try to be patient a little longer.

682
00:46:00,132 --> 00:46:01,867
The truth may be...

683
00:46:02,401 --> 00:46:05,070
different from what you think, Ms. Ham.

684
00:46:06,238 --> 00:46:09,175
Could that really be true?

685
00:46:10,709 --> 00:46:11,811
Let's wait and see.

686
00:46:13,579 --> 00:46:14,914
You're already moving...

687
00:46:14,914 --> 00:46:17,783
in a much better direction now.

688
00:46:23,756 --> 00:46:26,225
(Jigu Electronics)

689
00:46:28,928 --> 00:46:30,629
No, that's a lie.

690
00:46:31,230 --> 00:46:33,199
That day, that bastard brought...

691
00:46:33,199 --> 00:46:35,968
everything to our table himself
including the drinks and the food.

692
00:46:41,907 --> 00:46:44,877
What's that idiot babbling about?

693
00:46:44,877 --> 00:46:45,945
To leave no evidence,

694
00:46:45,945 --> 00:46:48,314
he left the card payments alone
and only took cash.

695
00:46:49,014 --> 00:46:51,584
And when he handed us over to that thug,
he probably got paid again.

696
00:46:51,584 --> 00:46:52,885
Double-dipped, basically.

697
00:46:52,885 --> 00:46:55,521
In all my years running a bar,

698
00:46:55,521 --> 00:46:57,590
now I'm getting treated
like a human trafficker.

699
00:47:01,727 --> 00:47:02,561
Sir.

700
00:47:03,863 --> 00:47:06,365
Nobody's going to eat you alive.

701
00:47:07,099 --> 00:47:08,501
You can wipe that look off your face.

702
00:47:10,870 --> 00:47:12,004
That handsome face.

703
00:47:12,671 --> 00:47:13,906
People might think...

704
00:47:14,573 --> 00:47:16,275
we've come to take your money.

705
00:47:19,778 --> 00:47:21,046
Will you all cut it out?

706
00:47:22,047 --> 00:47:24,817
If you're bored,
go somewhere else and get drunk.

707
00:47:25,217 --> 00:47:26,118
Why?

708
00:47:26,652 --> 00:47:27,987
Do you want me to introduce you
to a nice place?

709
00:47:33,592 --> 00:47:35,027
Sir, you're a funny guy.

710
00:47:52,545 --> 00:47:53,412
What,

711
00:47:54,280 --> 00:47:55,614
are you their fixer?

712
00:47:56,382 --> 00:47:57,716
And you're here to threaten me?

713
00:48:01,420 --> 00:48:02,488
Fine.

714
00:48:02,922 --> 00:48:04,890
I'm going to step into the kitchen now.

715
00:48:05,257 --> 00:48:06,592
I have to get ready for dinner service.

716
00:48:07,893 --> 00:48:09,728
But if I come back out here...

717
00:48:09,728 --> 00:48:11,330
and you're still pulling this crap,

718
00:48:13,899 --> 00:48:15,868
then I really won't be responsible
for what happens.

719
00:48:26,078 --> 00:48:27,880
That tiny little bastard.

720
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:29,315
Take the guest out.

721
00:48:32,284 --> 00:48:34,286
You're making a mistake here.

722
00:48:35,020 --> 00:48:37,823
A guy who runs a bar
sure can't read the room.

723
00:48:38,924 --> 00:48:40,726
That little...

724
00:48:45,931 --> 00:48:47,099
Damn it.

725
00:48:58,844 --> 00:49:00,146
If you make one more sound,

726
00:49:00,146 --> 00:49:01,580
I'll snap this arm clean off.

727
00:49:03,048 --> 00:49:06,285
Why is it that you Korean bastards
never listen when someone's being nice?

728
00:49:08,921 --> 00:49:11,390
Do I have to tell you again
what it is I want to know?

729
00:49:11,824 --> 00:49:13,292
No, I'll talk.

730
00:49:13,292 --> 00:49:15,294
I'll tell you everything.

731
00:49:20,833 --> 00:49:22,067
Were you trying to look stylish?

732
00:49:22,401 --> 00:49:23,302
Yes.

733
00:49:24,670 --> 00:49:27,540
Koreans are weird.

734
00:49:28,107 --> 00:49:32,144
(Reflection)

735
00:49:38,517 --> 00:49:39,752
Eyes down.

736
00:49:40,119 --> 00:49:43,022
I'll crush everyone whose eyes are open.

737
00:49:47,126 --> 00:49:48,027
Where am I?

738
00:49:52,464 --> 00:49:54,166
You've been given a special job today.

739
00:49:54,600 --> 00:49:56,902
Teach this little punk a lesson.

740
00:49:57,436 --> 00:49:59,271
He drugged our decent people...

741
00:49:59,271 --> 00:50:00,840
and extorted money.

742
00:50:01,340 --> 00:50:03,642
The boss approved it,
so do whatever you want.

743
00:50:03,976 --> 00:50:05,344
Is he one of ours?

744
00:50:05,344 --> 00:50:06,245
No.

745
00:50:06,512 --> 00:50:07,713
He's a Korean gangster.

746
00:50:07,713 --> 00:50:09,281
Can I really do whatever I want?

747
00:50:09,682 --> 00:50:11,250
Do whatever you want. I'm leaving.

748
00:50:11,250 --> 00:50:12,151
No.

749
00:50:13,219 --> 00:50:14,320
Please don't go.

750
00:50:15,254 --> 00:50:16,622
Please spare me.

751
00:50:17,223 --> 00:50:19,391
Let go, you fat bastard.

752
00:50:24,129 --> 00:50:25,097
Sir.

753
00:50:28,300 --> 00:50:29,235
Sir.

754
00:50:30,336 --> 00:50:31,270
Pinky.

755
00:50:31,270 --> 00:50:32,338
This little punk...

756
00:50:32,771 --> 00:50:35,140
is the younger brother
of the site manager who picks on you.

757
00:50:40,079 --> 00:50:41,180
Sir.

758
00:50:41,180 --> 00:50:42,548
Sir!

759
00:50:51,023 --> 00:50:52,491
Well, look who it is.

760
00:50:53,792 --> 00:50:57,563
I'm going to squeeze
all that grease out of your gut today.

761
00:51:07,540 --> 00:51:09,208
What took you so long?

762
00:51:09,208 --> 00:51:10,776
I seriously thought I was going to die.

763
00:51:11,644 --> 00:51:13,412
I used every personal contact I had...

764
00:51:13,412 --> 00:51:14,847
and managed to track him down.

765
00:51:14,847 --> 00:51:16,882
These days, privacy laws are stricter,

766
00:51:16,882 --> 00:51:18,217
so if you get caught, you're finished.

767
00:51:19,084 --> 00:51:20,920
And because of this,

768
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:23,022
I was not able to open the shop,
and normally, I'd bill that...

769
00:51:23,022 --> 00:51:25,624
You're sure it's Lee Jong Su, right?

770
00:51:25,624 --> 00:51:27,026
How many times do I have to tell you?

771
00:51:27,026 --> 00:51:28,594
I've been in this game for 30 years.

772
00:51:28,594 --> 00:51:29,461
Trust me.

773
00:51:29,862 --> 00:51:30,696
Right.

774
00:51:31,096 --> 00:51:32,965
Before I forget, take this first.

775
00:51:32,965 --> 00:51:34,466
I fixed it all, so it'll work fine now.

776
00:51:34,466 --> 00:51:36,068
Thank you.

777
00:51:37,770 --> 00:51:39,638
But is your real job
a repair shop owner...

778
00:51:39,638 --> 00:51:41,173
or a detective?

779
00:51:41,173 --> 00:51:44,009
Violent Crimes Unit One
at Dongdae Police Station.

780
00:51:44,009 --> 00:51:46,378
I'm the ace of the whole
major crimes squad.

781
00:51:46,745 --> 00:51:48,047
Then why...

782
00:51:49,248 --> 00:51:50,683
I did something and got fired.

783
00:51:51,984 --> 00:51:53,853
I didn't know that was that kind of money.

784
00:51:54,587 --> 00:51:56,322
After being unemployed
for about two years,

785
00:51:56,322 --> 00:51:57,756
my wife left with the kids,

786
00:51:58,290 --> 00:52:00,125
and she won't even give me a divorce.
It's driving me crazy.

787
00:52:02,094 --> 00:52:03,562
Did you get fired for taking bribes?

788
00:52:04,196 --> 00:52:06,298
Hey, what bribes?

789
00:52:06,699 --> 00:52:08,100
Don't go digging into the details.

790
00:52:12,872 --> 00:52:14,473
That's him.

791
00:52:18,410 --> 00:52:20,112
He's leaving now.

792
00:52:20,112 --> 00:52:21,514
You've seen this
in movies plenty of times, right?

793
00:52:21,514 --> 00:52:22,781
We're doing that now.

794
00:52:22,781 --> 00:52:23,616
Doing what?

795
00:52:23,616 --> 00:52:25,751
The good guys chasing the bad guy.

796
00:52:49,608 --> 00:52:51,677
But why is this car so slow?

797
00:52:52,144 --> 00:52:53,412
We're going to lose him.

798
00:52:53,412 --> 00:52:54,480
Lose him?

799
00:52:54,713 --> 00:52:56,715
With my driving,
this is already impressive.

800
00:52:58,484 --> 00:53:00,786
Lee Jong Su, that bastard.

801
00:53:01,787 --> 00:53:04,757
But what exactly is it
you need to find out from him?

802
00:53:05,157 --> 00:53:06,759
I want to do this job
knowing what's going on too.

803
00:53:08,194 --> 00:53:09,495
I can't tell you yet.

804
00:53:09,695 --> 00:53:10,830
You can't tell me?

805
00:53:10,830 --> 00:53:12,031
But you hired me for this case.

806
00:53:12,431 --> 00:53:14,166
You haven't forgotten who I am, have you?

807
00:53:14,633 --> 00:53:15,668
It's not that.

808
00:53:15,935 --> 00:53:17,436
I don't know yet either.

809
00:53:17,436 --> 00:53:18,504
What?

810
00:53:18,504 --> 00:53:20,072
You don't even know
why you're following him?

811
00:53:20,072 --> 00:53:22,174
I think Hee Su was being blackmailed.

812
00:53:22,975 --> 00:53:25,744
I asked what was going on,
but she wouldn't tell me.

813
00:53:25,978 --> 00:53:27,813
But Choi Hee Su is dead.

814
00:53:28,714 --> 00:53:31,650
Exactly, so we need to learn it
from the man who was threatening her.

815
00:53:31,650 --> 00:53:32,685
What are you talking about?

816
00:53:32,685 --> 00:53:34,587
You think that bastard
is just going to be easy?

817
00:53:35,120 --> 00:53:36,222
I don't have a choice.

818
00:53:36,689 --> 00:53:38,057
I have to find out, no matter what.

819
00:53:38,524 --> 00:53:39,859
With Choi Hee Su dead,

820
00:53:39,859 --> 00:53:41,060
what are you even going to do
once you know?

821
00:53:41,060 --> 00:53:42,795
The day Lee Jong Su came to the studio,

822
00:53:43,262 --> 00:53:44,697
both of them avoided me.

823
00:53:45,197 --> 00:53:46,098
Hey.

824
00:53:46,098 --> 00:53:48,467
Did I ever ask you for money like this?

825
00:53:48,467 --> 00:53:49,568
Who are you to give me money?

826
00:53:49,568 --> 00:53:50,636
Who do you think you are?

827
00:53:53,606 --> 00:53:54,440
Hey.

828
00:53:54,773 --> 00:53:56,108
- Who do you think you are to...
- No, Myo Jin, don't.

829
00:53:56,876 --> 00:53:59,044
Don't.

830
00:54:00,746 --> 00:54:02,548
- Hee Su.
- I'll contact you.

831
00:54:02,548 --> 00:54:04,316
I'll contact you. Just go.

832
00:54:10,456 --> 00:54:12,691
Choi Hee Su and Lee Jong Su? Why?

833
00:54:12,691 --> 00:54:14,660
He must know why that was.

834
00:54:15,494 --> 00:54:17,096
If both of them were avoiding me,

835
00:54:18,030 --> 00:54:19,665
then I must've been involved somehow.

836
00:54:19,665 --> 00:54:20,566
It better be true.

837
00:54:28,207 --> 00:54:29,041
I'm getting out.

838
00:54:51,297 --> 00:54:52,097
Did he go up?

839
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:56,335
He stopped on the second floor.

840
00:54:56,602 --> 00:54:57,903
There's no time. Use the stairs.

841
00:55:05,077 --> 00:55:06,212
Hey, hide yourself over here.

842
00:55:06,612 --> 00:55:08,147
He can't see you right now.

843
00:55:09,248 --> 00:55:12,051
But what exactly are we going to do
after following him in here like this?

844
00:55:13,919 --> 00:55:15,754
He's heading inside
after finishing his conversation.

845
00:55:18,557 --> 00:55:20,526
He has his photo hanging at the entrance,

846
00:55:20,826 --> 00:55:21,861
so I guess he's the owner.

847
00:55:22,394 --> 00:55:23,262
What is that?

848
00:55:23,496 --> 00:55:24,530
A wine bar?

849
00:55:24,830 --> 00:55:26,131
Give me a break.

850
00:55:27,099 --> 00:55:28,067
But...

851
00:55:29,034 --> 00:55:30,669
where did that bastard
get that kind of money?

852
00:55:30,669 --> 00:55:32,705
What do we do now?

853
00:55:35,508 --> 00:55:36,475
Take this first.

854
00:55:37,143 --> 00:55:38,344
What's this?

855
00:55:38,777 --> 00:55:40,146
It's a cloning kit.

856
00:55:40,146 --> 00:55:41,580
Just plug in this cable,

857
00:55:41,580 --> 00:55:43,616
and the light comes on
and starts the copy.

858
00:55:43,883 --> 00:55:44,984
No matter how much data's on it,

859
00:55:44,984 --> 00:55:46,385
cloning a phone only takes about a minute.

860
00:55:47,453 --> 00:55:48,754
No.

861
00:55:48,754 --> 00:55:49,722
Was it two minutes?

862
00:55:49,722 --> 00:55:51,090
Anyway, simple, right?

863
00:55:51,090 --> 00:55:52,558
You want me to clone his phone?

864
00:55:52,992 --> 00:55:54,326
By myself?

865
00:55:54,860 --> 00:55:56,495
If you want to know about someone,

866
00:55:56,495 --> 00:55:58,297
you look at their phone.

867
00:55:58,297 --> 00:56:00,399
A person's whole life is in there.

868
00:56:00,399 --> 00:56:02,334
What if I get caught?

869
00:56:02,701 --> 00:56:03,802
I can't do something like this.

870
00:56:04,837 --> 00:56:05,704
Come on.

871
00:56:05,704 --> 00:56:07,339
So what, you're going
to walk up to him and say,

872
00:56:07,339 --> 00:56:10,009
"Hey, why were you threatening my friend?"

873
00:56:10,009 --> 00:56:12,244
And then he'll go,
"Well, here's the thing..."

874
00:56:12,244 --> 00:56:13,512
You think he'll answer like that?

875
00:56:13,512 --> 00:56:15,047
This is the only way...

876
00:56:15,047 --> 00:56:17,683
to find out what that bastard was up to.

877
00:56:20,085 --> 00:56:21,954
Then what am I supposed to do?

878
00:56:21,954 --> 00:56:24,356
First, figure out which room he's in.

879
00:56:24,356 --> 00:56:25,491
Come on, hurry.

880
00:56:25,491 --> 00:56:26,926
Go. Quick.

881
00:56:26,926 --> 00:56:27,726
But...

882
00:56:33,732 --> 00:56:34,733
Welcome.

883
00:56:36,769 --> 00:56:37,670
This way, please.

884
00:56:44,810 --> 00:56:46,912
Excuse me, where is the owner?

885
00:56:46,912 --> 00:56:48,681
He's in a consultation right now.

886
00:56:48,681 --> 00:56:49,849
Would you like me to let him know?

887
00:56:49,849 --> 00:56:52,384
No, it's okay. I can wait until he's done.

888
00:56:52,384 --> 00:56:54,253
Okay. Please call me when you've decided.

889
00:57:14,740 --> 00:57:16,742
You look even better
than the last time you came.

890
00:57:16,742 --> 00:57:17,476
Really?

891
00:57:17,476 --> 00:57:18,811
Then I guess the money was worth it.

892
00:57:20,579 --> 00:57:22,481
I look forward to your choice.

893
00:57:22,948 --> 00:57:24,416
Of course, I'll invest in it.

894
00:57:24,917 --> 00:57:26,986
Thanks to you again,

895
00:57:26,986 --> 00:57:29,054
I think everything
will go smoothly this time too.

896
00:57:32,892 --> 00:57:35,261
Hey! Who's the owner here?

897
00:57:35,461 --> 00:57:36,729
Get out here right now.

898
00:57:36,729 --> 00:57:38,264
Is it you?

899
00:57:38,264 --> 00:57:40,432
Excuse me, what seems to be the problem?

900
00:57:40,666 --> 00:57:41,634
I see.

901
00:57:42,201 --> 00:57:43,602
- So it's you.
- Goodness.

902
00:57:43,602 --> 00:57:45,371
You're the bastard...

903
00:57:45,371 --> 00:57:47,173
who talked my wife into divorcing me.

904
00:57:47,173 --> 00:57:48,641
What did you do to her...

905
00:57:48,641 --> 00:57:51,343
for her to slap divorce papers
down at the breakfast table?

906
00:57:51,343 --> 00:57:52,278
You bastard!

907
00:57:52,278 --> 00:57:53,379
Sir,

908
00:57:53,379 --> 00:57:55,614
you can't behave like this in here.

909
00:57:55,614 --> 00:57:57,283
Please calm down first,

910
00:57:57,283 --> 00:57:59,385
and let's go over there
and talk this through.

911
00:57:59,385 --> 00:58:00,352
Talk this through?

912
00:58:00,352 --> 00:58:01,353
Talk this through?

913
00:58:01,353 --> 00:58:03,189
Don't give me
that "talk this through" bullshit.

914
00:58:03,189 --> 00:58:05,324
And why am I your customer?

915
00:58:05,324 --> 00:58:06,458
I'm your customer's husband.

916
00:58:06,458 --> 00:58:08,527
The husband of the customer you seduced.

917
00:58:08,994 --> 00:58:09,962
Phone.

918
00:58:09,962 --> 00:58:11,263
What are you doing?

919
00:58:11,263 --> 00:58:12,531
You slept with my wife, didn't you?

920
00:58:12,531 --> 00:58:13,833
You thought I wouldn't know?

921
00:58:13,833 --> 00:58:15,201
Look at you. You can't even answer.

922
00:58:15,467 --> 00:58:16,936
You picked the wrong person, you bastard.

923
00:58:18,470 --> 00:58:19,772
How many times was it?

924
00:58:20,206 --> 00:58:22,208
How many times did you do it?

925
00:58:25,611 --> 00:58:26,479
Hey.

926
00:58:26,712 --> 00:58:29,315
My wife's eyes were so bloodshot
she went to the hospital,

927
00:58:29,315 --> 00:58:31,684
and they said she was addicted to wine,
you bastard!

928
00:58:31,684 --> 00:58:34,019
I'm saying, first let go of this,
and then we can talk.

929
00:58:34,453 --> 00:58:36,555
- What are you doing? Get him off me.
- Yes, sir.

930
00:58:36,555 --> 00:58:37,857
Don't do this.

931
00:58:37,857 --> 00:58:38,891
You ruined me,

932
00:58:38,891 --> 00:58:40,726
took my wife and my money,

933
00:58:40,726 --> 00:58:41,894
and you think you'll get away with it?

934
00:58:41,894 --> 00:58:43,162
You really messed
with the wrong guy, you bastard.

935
00:58:43,162 --> 00:58:44,396
What are you even saying?

936
00:58:44,930 --> 00:58:46,332
Hey, let go of this.

937
00:58:46,332 --> 00:58:48,701
I'm going to throw all of you in prison.

938
00:58:48,701 --> 00:58:49,502
Let go.

939
00:58:50,035 --> 00:58:51,003
Come on.

940
00:58:51,003 --> 00:58:52,938
(Downloading 31 percent)

941
00:58:55,341 --> 00:58:56,275
What do I do?

942
00:58:57,009 --> 00:58:58,744
My luck is terrible today.

943
00:58:58,744 --> 00:59:00,980
Of all days,
some complete psycho has to show up.

944
00:59:00,980 --> 00:59:02,414
(Downloading 46 percent)

945
00:59:02,414 --> 00:59:04,216
Get over here!
Where are you running off to?

946
00:59:04,216 --> 00:59:06,752
Hey, you!
You slept with my wife, didn't you?

947
00:59:06,752 --> 00:59:08,053
You thought I wouldn't know?

948
00:59:08,053 --> 00:59:09,321
Look at you. You can't even answer.

949
00:59:10,189 --> 00:59:11,090
Come on.

950
00:59:12,691 --> 00:59:14,426
How many times?

951
00:59:14,426 --> 00:59:15,194
How many times did you do it?

952
00:59:15,194 --> 00:59:16,662
So you really did sleep with her?

953
00:59:16,662 --> 00:59:17,630
Hey.

954
00:59:19,265 --> 00:59:20,299
You little...

955
00:59:20,299 --> 00:59:21,200
Let go!

956
00:59:22,768 --> 00:59:23,836
(Uploading 82 percent)

957
00:59:27,706 --> 00:59:28,507
(Uploading 96 percent)

958
00:59:31,977 --> 00:59:32,945
Who are you?

959
00:59:33,712 --> 00:59:34,513
What?

960
00:59:36,282 --> 00:59:37,550
Well...

961
00:59:40,452 --> 00:59:42,388
How reckless of you to come here.

962
00:59:42,855 --> 00:59:44,023
Let go of this.

963
00:59:44,023 --> 00:59:45,758
Just let go.

964
00:59:45,758 --> 00:59:47,560
I'm a cop.

965
00:59:47,827 --> 00:59:50,062
Boss, this person's a cop.

966
00:59:51,363 --> 00:59:52,598
- What?
- You're all dead today.

967
00:59:52,598 --> 00:59:53,833
You assaulted a police officer.

968
00:59:53,833 --> 00:59:54,834
You little...

969
00:59:54,834 --> 00:59:55,968
What? Let go of that.

970
01:00:00,072 --> 01:00:00,873
Sir.

971
01:00:08,247 --> 01:00:09,315
Sir.

972
01:00:09,315 --> 01:00:10,249
Are you okay?

973
01:00:12,218 --> 01:00:13,819
Wang Gi Cheol, that bastard.

974
01:00:14,186 --> 01:00:15,554
We can't let him get away now.

975
01:00:16,388 --> 01:00:17,690
Okay.

976
01:00:20,292 --> 01:00:21,093
Damn it.

977
01:00:25,598 --> 01:00:26,732
Mr. Lee Jong Su.

978
01:00:36,575 --> 01:00:37,476
Hey.

979
01:00:37,476 --> 01:00:38,644
Just a second.

980
01:00:45,618 --> 01:00:46,452
Damn it.

981
01:00:52,291 --> 01:00:53,225
Damn it!

982
01:00:53,492 --> 01:00:54,860
I have something to ask you.

983
01:00:55,561 --> 01:00:56,795
It'll just take a second.

984
01:01:15,181 --> 01:01:16,015
Excuse me.

985
01:01:18,384 --> 01:01:19,351
You vicious bitch.

986
01:01:21,487 --> 01:01:22,488
Wasn't it enough...

987
01:01:23,389 --> 01:01:24,623
that two people died?

988
01:01:26,892 --> 01:01:28,127
You could've stopped there...

989
01:01:29,161 --> 01:01:30,196
with your revenge.

990
01:02:11,136 --> 01:02:15,207
(REVERSE)

991
01:02:15,407 --> 01:02:16,575
Check what messages they exchanged,

992
01:02:16,575 --> 01:02:18,043
and the answer will be clear.

993
01:02:18,043 --> 01:02:20,012
You killed my mom and dad?

994
01:02:20,012 --> 01:02:22,848
I didn't think she'd find out this fast.

995
01:02:22,848 --> 01:02:24,850
Then what am I supposed to do?

996
01:02:25,284 --> 01:02:26,418
Stop her.

997
01:02:26,418 --> 01:02:28,621
You handled the Jebudo Island
villa explosion case, didn't you?

998
01:02:28,621 --> 01:02:30,789
It was all complete bullshit.

999
01:02:30,789 --> 01:02:32,158
You don't need to be curious.

1000
01:02:32,158 --> 01:02:34,059
If you know, it puts us both in danger.

1001
01:02:34,059 --> 01:02:35,227
Thanks to that, it all clicked.

1002
01:02:35,227 --> 01:02:38,063
I now know what was happening
without me knowing.

1003
01:02:39,064 --> 01:02:40,900
There's someone else besides us...

1004
01:02:40,900 --> 01:02:42,234
who's after Ham Myo Jin?

1005
01:02:43,422 --> 01:02:45,422
